<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-01-08T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-01-08T15:00:00-05:00" n="564" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d564">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">632.006/1–245: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Donnelly</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-01-08T16:00:00-04:00">January 8,
                                    1945—4 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>68. Reurtel 15, January 2, 1944 [<hi rend="italic">1945</hi>]. The
                            Department welcomes the reduction in the number of commodities listed
                            for inclusion in the proposed import control law but remains greatly
                            concerned about its possible effects.</p>
                        <p>If the Brazilian Government remains firm in its determination to adopt
                            this measure, the Embassy is requested to endeavor to persuade the
                            authorities at least to include in the decree a provision that will
                            clearly identify the control as a war measure, subject to removal at the
                            close of hostilities.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>